314
00:25:34,106 --> 00:25:36,525
- What about your brother?
- Billy?

315
00:25:36,608 --> 00:25:39,695
I know he thinks I hate him,
but I don't.

316
00:25:39,778 --> 00:25:43,699
I just wasn't a very good sister.
I was runnin' wild.

317
00:25:43,782 --> 00:25:47,619
- Is he still in St. Charles?
- Last I heard.

318
00:25:47,702 --> 00:25:50,288
He's almost 22.

319
00:25:50,372 --> 00:25:52,749
His birthday's in April.

320
00:25:52,832 --> 00:25:55,627
Were you close?

321
00:25:55,710 --> 00:25:58,254
Well, we had different fathers.

322
00:25:58,338 --> 00:26:01,215
Neither one of us knew 'em.

323
00:26:01,299 --> 00:26:03,968
After my mama died,
it was just us.

324
00:26:04,052 --> 00:26:06,804
Yeah, you were, uh, what, 16?

325
00:26:08,264 --> 00:26:11,642
Yeah. She died two days
after my 16th birthday.

326
00:26:13,686 --> 00:26:15,729
What was she like?

327
00:26:17,815 --> 00:26:20,192
Pretty. Wild.

328
00:26:21,860 --> 00:26:25,781
When she was feelin' good,
she could be a lot of fun.

329
00:26:25,864 --> 00:26:28,200
She wasn't like
anybody's mama I knew.

330
00:26:28,283 --> 00:26:31,787
We were more like sisters,
I guess.

331
00:26:31,870 --> 00:26:36,750
She just couldn't stay clean. I guess
