Look, I prosecuted this case.

667
00:48:55,124 --> 00:48:58,252
It was my first big case,
and I know it cold.

668
00:48:58,336 --> 00:49:01,213
The attorney general's office is totally
behind us, and so is the public...

669
00:49:01,297 --> 00:49:03,341
and we're gonna see
this sentence carried out.

670
00:49:03,424 --> 00:49:09,263
Now, you can dick around all you want,
but this sentence will be carried out.

671
00:49:09,346 --> 00:49:11,807
It's good to see you, Joe.

672
00:49:30,325 --> 00:49:35,830
"...call our grandfather
Grandpa."

673
00:49:40,835 --> 00:49:42,795
Frances?

674
00:49:44,088 --> 00:49:46,007
Frances?

675
00:49:48,175 --> 00:49:50,678
What time is it, Frances?

676
00:49:50,761 --> 00:49:54,557
3.30. Saturday hours are over.

677
00:49:55,683 --> 00:49:58,477
Shit.

678
00:49:58,560 --> 00:50:00,604
Ain't no man worth
gettin' upset over.

679
00:50:00,688 --> 00:50:02,606
Shut up.

680
00:50:02,689 --> 00:50:06,526
You wanna get mad, I can give you
a lot better things to get mad about.

681
00:50:06,610 --> 00:50:09,946
- Just stay out of it, bitch!
- Who you callin' bitch, bitch?

682
00:50:10,030 --> 00:50:12,157
Calling' you bitch,
you stupid bitch!

683
00:50:12,240 --> 00:50:14,951
You think anybody's gonna marry you
after you killed two husbands?

684
00:50:15,035 --> 00:50:17,787
At least I ever got married.
That's more than you can say.

685
00:50:17,871 --> 00:50:21,875
- Shut up!
- Girl, you losin' your mind.

686
00:50:32,468 --> 00:50:35,680
...since the tender age
of 12 years old.

687
00:50:35,763 --> 00:50:41,310
Carrie says that men are stupid,
and Carrie specializes in...

688
00:50:44,980 --> 00:50:46,982
Hey.

689
00:50:48,150 --> 00:50:50,944
Didn't think you were comin'.

690
00:50:51,028 --> 00:50:53,322
Well, I was out of town.

691
00:50:53,405 --> 00:50:55,616
So much for promises.

692
00:50:55,699 --> 00:50:58,201
I was doing interviews
for your report.

693
00:50:58,285 --> 00:51:00,370
Then I guess you know
everything now.

694
00:51:00,454 --> 00:51:03,164
No, I know about the past.

695
00:51:03,248 --> 00:51:05,208
You're not that person any more.

696
00:51:10,296 --> 00:51:14,050
All right, look, I need you
to tell me about that night.

697
00:51:16,594 --> 00:51:18,763
That night?

698
00:51:23,267 --> 00:51:25,186
That night is...

699
00:51:25,978 --> 00:51:28,105
inside me like this...

700
00:51:29,940 --> 00:51:32,026
big, terrible shadow.

701
00:51:35,404 --> 00:51:37,698
I hated Debbie Hunt.

702
00:51:37,781 --> 00:51:41,577
I hated everything,
everything I didn't have.

703
00:51:43,161 --> 00:51:47,165
And Debbie Hunt used to just
rub my nose in it.

704
00:51:48,667 --> 00:51:50,710
And all that hate...

705
00:51:50,794 --> 00:51:53,713
just blew everything apart.

706
00:51:55,924 --> 00:51:58,051
I killed them.

707
00:51:58,134 --> 00:52:00,219
I killed myself.

708
00:52:00,303 --> 00:52:02,221
I know what I did.

709
00:52:03,556 --> 00:52:05,975
I can't change that.

710
00:52:06,058 --> 00:52:08,811
I can only change myself.

711
00:52:10,479 --> 00:52:14,066
Uh, I guess there are just...

712
00:52:14,150 --> 00:52:16,068
some things...

713
00:52:16,152 --> 00:52:18,404
can't be forgiven.

714
00:52:18,487 --> 00:52:21,240
Why not...

715
00:52:21,323 --> 00:52:24,368
if a person's able to change?

716
00:52:24,451 --> 00:52:28,413
'Cause the people doin' the
forgivin' have to change too.

717
00:52:41,509 --> 00:52:44,762
Today for the first time
in my term as Governor...

718
00:52:44,846 --> 00:52:47,390
in light of a number
of most-compelling reasons...

719
00:52:47,473 --> 00:52:50,393
I am granting clemency
in a capital case.

720
00:52:54,689 --> 00:52:59,235
I'm withdrawing my order of
execution for John Henry Reese...

721
00:52:59,360 --> 00:53:03,280
and commuting his sentence
to life imprisonment.

722
00:53:03,405 --> 00:53:06,242
- What about Liggett?
- There should be no mistake however...
- No.

723
00:53:06,325 --> 00:53:09,912
- That I remain a strong proponent
of the death penalty...
- Why?

724
00:53:10,037 --> 00:53:13,290
- And a firm believer of its place in our society.
- What the hell do you want, a religious conversion?

725
00:53:13,373 --> 00:53:16,543
- Wouldn't have hurt.
- And I know the people of this state...

726
00:53:16,668 --> 00:53:19,755
overwhelmingly agree with me.

727
00:53:19,838 --> 00:53:22,132
- There are, however...
- Look...

728
00:53:22,257 --> 00:53:25,260
- those rare occasions when
exceptions cry out.
- It's an issue of credibility.

729
00:53:25,343 --> 00:53:27,387
- And the rule of law...
- Whose credibility?
- Mine.

730
00:53:27,512 --> 00:53:30,932
Must acknowledge
extraordinary circumstances.

731
00:53:31,015 --> 00:53:33,768
- I'll take a few questions now.
- Governor.
- Governor.

732
00:53:33,851 --> 00:53:37,522
Governor, could you tell us
the compelling reasons
that prompted your decision...

733
00:53:37,647 --> 00:53:40,483
to commute
Mr Reese's sentence?

734
00:53:40,566 --> 00:53:45,529
- Mr Reese has gone as far as any prisoner I've ever seen...
- I stick my neck out, there better be a damn good reason.

735
00:53:45,613 --> 00:53:51,285
- Transforming himself into a thinking, contributing...
- I don't see it with Liggett. Maybe you do. I'm sorry.

736
00:53:51,368 --> 00:53:54,371
- This is about reelection, isn't it?
- Responsible and very unique voice.

737
00:53:54,496 --> 00:53:57,041
It's about getting
the black vote, isn't it?

738
00:53:57,124 --> 00:53:59,334
It's about clemency.

739
00:54:00,752 --> 00:54:03,463
Governor, what about
the Liggett case?

740
00:54:03,547 --> 00:54:07,843
Clemency was denied. Miss Liggett's
death warrant is set to be carried out...

741
00:54:07,968 --> 00:54:12,264
at 12.01 a.m. On Saturday,
one week from today.

742
00:54:12,389 --> 00:54:16,851
If it's carried out, Cindy Liggett will be
the first woman in 11 years...

743
00:54:16,935 --> 00:54:18,895
to be executed in this state.

744
00:54:19,020 --> 00:54:23,733
- Any comment?
- Miss Liggett committed a brutal
and senseless double murder.

745
00:54:23,858 --> 00:54:27,862
Her sex made no difference to her victims.
It makes no difference to us
under our legal system.

746
00:54:39,248 --> 00:54:43,419
- It's okay.
- I'm sorry.

747
00:54:43,502 --> 00:54:45,212
I know.

748
00:54:51,969 --> 00:54:54,346
Look, I've got an idea
for an appeal.

749
00:54:54,471 --> 00:54:57,891
No, no. You've gotta keep
letting me fight this.

750
00:55:00,894 --> 00:55:03,355
I am afraid to say no...

751
00:55:03,438 --> 00:55:06,065
and I am afraid to say yes.

752
00:55:10,737 --> 00:55:12,864
Look.

753
00:55:14,532 --> 00:55:17,159
There is somethin'
you can do for me.

754
00:55:25,417 --> 00:55:27,628
- One, two, three, hey!
- What's this about?

755
00:55:27,711 --> 00:55:29,838
- One, two, three, hey!
- I'm a friend of your sister's.

756
00:55:29,964 --> 00:55:32,716
- One, two, three, hey!
- Here's how it is.

757
00:55:32,800 --> 00:55:37,846
Uh, she's got six more days, okay?
Maybe you already know that.

758
00:55:37,930 --> 00:55:40,307
Now she wanted me
to get you this.

759
00:55:43,977 --> 00:55:47,314
You're the only family she's got.

760
00:55:47,397 --> 00:55:50,150
She loves you.

761
00:55:50,275 --> 00:55:53,111
- She said that?
- Yes, she did.

762
00:55:53,194 --> 00:55:56,197
You'll be doin' K.P., boy!
Let's move it!

763
00:55:56,322 --> 00:55:59,492
Six days.

764
00:55:59,575 --> 00:56:02,411
We're doin' all we can.

765
00:56:05,081 --> 00:56:07,124
I'm the one who turned her in.
Did you know that?

766
00:56:07,249 --> 00:56:09,627
Look, she doesn't hold anything
against you, okay?

767
00:56:09,710 --> 00:56:12,671
She's... She's actually grateful that
you stopped her. Believe me.

768
00:56:12,755 --> 00:56:17,051
- The cops, they, um... they said
I'd be savin' her life.
- Yep.

769
00:56:17,176 --> 00:56:19,720
What I did,
I did it to help her.

770
00:56:19,803 --> 00:56:23,932
She was all messed up. Couldn't
tell what she was gonna do next.

771
00:56:24,016 --> 00:56:26,476
I didn't know this
was gonna happen.

772
00:56:26,560 --> 00:56:30,063
Listen, she knows all that,
all of it.

773
00:56:30,188 --> 00:56:32,482
She's okay.

774
00:56:40,615 --> 00:56:42,575
Come on, boys! Move it!

775
00:56:42,700 --> 00:56:47,497
So my next trick, kids,
is very impressive, very exciting.

776
00:56:47,580 --> 00:56:51,876
What I'm going to do is show you
a beautiful bouquet of flowers.

777
00:56:51,959 --> 00:56:54,003
- Would ya like to see that?
- Yeah.

778
00:56:54,086 --> 00:56:57,590
Would ya? Okay. Good.
Hold on. Ah, here they are.

779
00:56:57,715 --> 00:57:02,261
Aren't they beautiful?
As you can see, there's blue...

780
00:57:02,386 --> 00:57:04,680
and red and pink.

781
00:57:04,763 --> 00:57:08,976
What's so funny? Why are you giggling?
What do you mean there's no flowers?

782
00:57:09,101 --> 00:57:12,271
- Hi, I'm Rick Hayes. Remember?
- This happens to be my home.

783
00:57:12,396 --> 00:57:14,856
- Look, I, I need your help. I'm sorr...
- It's my daughter's birthday.

784
00:57:14,940 --> 00:57:20,695
Okay. Well, I need you to file a stay of
execution in Federal District Court
for Cindy Liggett.

785
00:57:20,820 --> 00:57:24,741
- Mama, Vanessa took my M&Ms.
- Okay, sweetheart, go back.
I'll take care of it.

786
00:57:24,824 --> 00:57:26,451
- Okay.
- I'll be right there.

787
00:57:26,534 --> 00:57:29,621
L-I'm sorry. But we... we have some
big-time grounds for appeal here.

788
00:57:29,704 --> 00:57:34,083
- What grounds?
- Well, ineffective counsel.
Basically, your partner Ed Duffy blew it.

789
00:57:34,208 --> 00:57:38,254
- Oh, you got a hell of a nerve.
- All right. Well, you take a look
at this, uh...

790
00:57:40,256 --> 00:57:42,133
I've got a police report here, okay?

791
00:57:42,216 --> 00:57:45,386
And this is a statement made by
her brother before the arrest.

792
00:57:47,596 --> 00:57:51,100
She and Doug Barnes had been
up for two days smokin' crack.
Now, he never introduced it.

793
00:57:51,183 --> 00:57:53,143
You tell me why.

794
00:57:53,227 --> 00:57:57,064
Well, I don't know. Maybe he felt a jury
sees a drug addict as subhuman.

795
00:57:57,147 --> 00:58:00,233
You and I both know they'd be a lot more
likely to execute an addict.

796
00:58:00,359 --> 00:58:03,362
Hey, we're talkin' a level of intoxication
here that might save her life.

797
00:58:03,487 --> 00:58:05,864
- Oh, man, it was a strategic move.
- Oh, come on.

798
00:58:05,989 --> 00:58:08,992
- Maybe he should have
pressed the drugs.
- We're six days from her execution.

799
00:58:09,075 --> 00:58:12,746
This is the only chance
she's got.

800
00:58:12,871 --> 00:58:17,750
Will you do it? Look, I'll handle
the research. I'll do the legwork.

801
00:58:17,834 --> 00:58:22,213
- Mom, I wanna open my presents.
- In a minute, baby. In a minute.

802
00:58:22,338 --> 00:58:25,341
One, two, three.

803
00:58:25,424 --> 00:58:28,219
Abracadabra.

804
00:58:28,302 --> 00:58:31,389
- I'll do my own research.
- Good.

805
00:58:35,809 --> 00:58:37,937
Good night.

806
00:59:18,059 --> 00:59:20,603
Good evening, sir.

807
00:59:20,728 --> 00:59:22,688
Thanks.

808
00:59:29,695 --> 00:59:31,989
Nice to see you.

809
00:59:34,950 --> 00:59:36,660
- Hey.
- Hey.

810
00:59:36,785 --> 00:59:38,995
- You made it.
- Yeah, I'm sorry I'm late, sweetie.

811
00:59:39,121 --> 00:59:42,791
Well, you missed the soggy crab cakes
and the California champagne.

812
00:59:42,874 --> 00:59:45,251
- Well, you look beautiful, though.
- Thank you.

813
00:59:45,377 --> 00:59:47,921
- Hey, here's John.
- There he is.

814
00:59:48,046 --> 00:59:50,423
- Hi. - Hi, how ya doin'?
- I'm good. You? - You okay?

815
00:59:50,548 --> 00:59:54,927
- Yeah, everything's good.
- You free on Sunday, maybe
for some tennis or whatever?

816
00:59:55,011 --> 00:59:57,555
Uh, yeah. Maybe.

817
01:00:02,101 --> 01:00:04,228
Rick?

818
01:00:04,312 --> 01:00:07,648
- They spent hundreds of thousands
on the building alone.
- Governor? Governor?

819
01:00:07,773 --> 01:00:10,776
- Excuse me, sir. Hi. Um, I'd like to...
- Mr Hayes.

820
01:00:10,860 --> 01:00:13,070
- Yes, sir.
- Clemency.
- Yes.

821
01:00:13,153 --> 01:00:15,906
You fellas did a mighty
fine job on the Reese case.

822
01:00:16,031 --> 01:00:19,201
- Thank you, sir. I'd like to talk to you
about Cindy Liggett.
- Liggett?

823
01:00:19,284 --> 01:00:23,121
- Yes. I urge you to reconsider. - Oh, not now.
- I believe that this woman deserves clemency as well.

824
01:00:23,205 --> 01:00:25,415
- This is completely inappropriate.
- It's all right.
- No, it isn't all right.

825
01:00:25,540 --> 01:00:28,627
- We'll talk tomorrow in my office.
John, set that up.
- She had ineffective counsel.

826
01:00:28,752 --> 01:00:30,712
- She should've been given a life sentence.
- I'm sorry.
- Shut up.

827
01:00:30,795 --> 01:00:33,465
- Prison is the only stable environment...
- This is difficult for all of us, Mr Hayes.

828
01:00:33,548 --> 01:00:37,051
- That this woman has ever known. Her life outside...
- Rick, come on.
- John, let go of me.

829
01:00:37,135 --> 01:00:40,305
Her life outside was a nightmare.
She's changed. She's grown.

830
01:00:40,388 --> 01:00:44,767
She's a different person now. Now,
we're... we're not settin' an example here.

831
01:00:44,892 --> 01:00:48,563
We never gave her a chance to become
like us, sir! We've become like her.

832
01:00:48,646 --> 01:00:51,732
You have an eloquent tongue, Mr Hayes.
Must run in the family.

833
01:00:51,816 --> 01:00:55,486
- Well, Cindy Liggett didn't have a chance,
sir. And if you'd just...
- Now, you've had your turn!

834
01:00:55,611 --> 01:00:58,948
Now, the rule of law demands that
this girl receive the maximum penalty
for what she did.

835
01:00:59,073 --> 01:01:02,034
- Governor, you...
- May I finish?

836
01:01:02,117 --> 01:01:06,121
- Yes.
- Now, if you don't like this particular law,
by all means, change it.

837
01:01:06,205 --> 01:01:10,500
But in the meantime, it's my sworn duty
as governor to uphold the laws
as I find them.

838
01:01:10,625 --> 01:01:14,212
You understand? You just pour
yourself a good, stiff drink.

839
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:18,008
- Enjoy the rest of the party
with your brother John.
- Sir.

840
01:01:18,091 --> 01:01:21,761
- Let's go.
- Mark, I'm sorry about that.
Now, the building...

841
01:01:21,845 --> 01:01:24,848
Young turks.

842
01:01:24,973 --> 01:01:28,393
- I hope you know what you just did.
- John, the man pulls the switch.
Bottom line.

843
01:01:28,476 --> 01:01:31,229
- Quiet. Quiet. Quiet. Quiet.
- Look, I don't care who hears this.

844
01:01:31,312 --> 01:01:34,565
- What the hell is wrong with you?
- For what? Do you think this is about me?

845
01:01:34,649 --> 01:01:36,359
- Do you know what you're doing?
- Yeah.

846
01:01:36,442 --> 01:01:39,195
- You're ruining your life and mine too.
- What about her life?

847
01:01:39,278 --> 01:01:41,405
- You can't change what's gonna happen.
- Then you try and stop me.

848
01:01:41,530 --> 01:01:43,407
- I'm trying. Believe me, I'm trying.
- Uh-huh.

849
01:01:43,532 --> 01:01:46,702
I kept you from being disbarred after
that mess with Dad, but I don't know.

850
01:01:46,827 --> 01:01:49,913
- You've got me on this one, brother.
- What are you talkin' about?

851
01:01:49,997 --> 01:01:54,710
- John, you think this is about us?
You and me?
- You tell me.

852
01:01:54,793 --> 01:01:59,089
You are so way off. This is the first thing
ever that is not about you and me.

853
01:02:09,557 --> 01:02:12,310
I figured I'd save you
the trouble.

854
01:02:14,354 --> 01:02:16,397
I'm sorry.

855
01:02:16,481 --> 01:02:20,693
Don't be.
And congratulations on Reese.

856
01:02:22,069 --> 01:02:27,033
You were right.
There's a first time for everything.

857
01:02:27,116 --> 01:02:30,536
She has unlimited visiting time.
You know that, don't you?

858
01:02:30,619 --> 01:02:34,873
Then I'd better get goin'.
Sam, thanks.

859
01:02:34,957 --> 01:02:38,127
- Thanks?
- Hey, I don't regret anything
that's happened here.

860
01:02:38,210 --> 01:02:41,380
It's the next four days
I'm worried about.

861
01:02:42,923 --> 01:02:45,842
I wish I could tell you
something that would help, but...

862
01:02:45,926 --> 01:02:49,095
- Well, there is somethin' you could do.
- What's that?

863
01:02:49,221 --> 01:02:51,348
Well, her brother's up
at Walkerton Work Camp.

864
01:02:51,473 --> 01:02:55,643
Now, if you could get him a visit with her,
that would mean a lot.

865
01:02:55,727 --> 01:02:59,230
- I'll see what I can do.
- Well, that'd be great.

866
01:02:59,314 --> 01:03:01,524
- See y'all.
- Bye, Rick.

867
01:03:18,791 --> 01:03:21,877
- Hey, how's it goin'?
- I tried to reach you at the office.

868
01:03:22,002 --> 01:03:24,296
- We heard on the appeal?
- We got turned down.

869
01:03:24,421 --> 01:03:26,799
- Shit!
- This came this morning.

870
01:03:26,882 --> 01:03:29,509
- No hearing, nothing. Just a ruling.
- Man.

871
01:03:29,593 --> 01:03:34,056
Our next move should be Judge Gorman
on the Federal Court of Appeals.
He's a good guy.

872
01:03:34,181 --> 01:03:36,141
- Who's that, Gorman?
- Yeah, Gorman.

873
01:03:36,266 --> 01:03:39,603
- They're in recess now.
Can you track him down?
- Yeah, l-I'll get to work on it.

874
01:03:39,686 --> 01:03:43,982
Look, uh, you should know I left the job.
I have no authority any more.

875
01:03:44,065 --> 01:03:48,528
Well, great. Now that you're no longer a
third-rate bureaucrat, you can really help.

876
01:03:48,611 --> 01:03:50,905
Well, let's hope so.

877
01:03:52,573 --> 01:03:55,660
Mrs Gorman, I promise you I would not be
calling you at your home at this hour...

878
01:03:55,785 --> 01:03:57,745
if it weren't urgent.

879
01:03:57,870 --> 01:04:01,624
No, l-I understand. It's-It's...
It's his vacation, but...

880
01:04:01,749 --> 01:04:05,252
Well... No, I'm...
I'm sorry, but...

881
01:04:05,377 --> 01:04:07,504
Well, all right.

882
01:04:07,630 --> 01:04:11,133
Uh, look, I'm sorry
to have bothered you.

883
01:04:12,468 --> 01:04:15,470
- Hi.
- Remember me?

884
01:04:15,596 --> 01:04:18,056
I've got a fully-stocked bar now.

